productEmsList.title: Pin Count
productEmsList.tooltip: Match the pin count on the sonar port of your sounder

productEmsList.title: Installation
productEmsList.tooltip:
Transom Mount: These are attached to the back (transom) of a boat hull. Alternatively, use the included equipment to install on a trolling motor.

In-hull: An in-hull transducer is installed inside a boat hull against the bottom

productEmsList.title: Tradition Sonar
productEmsList.tooltip:
77/200 kHz sonar transmits a single ping at either 77 or 200 kHz 

50/200 kHz sonar transmits a single ping at either 50 or 200 kHz 

High-wide CHIRP has a frequncy range of 150-240 kHz in each transmission

productEmsList.title: ClearVü
productEmsList.tooltip:
260/455 kHz ClearVü is ideal for deeper water,  1000' Max Depth scanning sonar

455/800 kHz is the most flexible scanning sonar up to 500' max depth

Ultra-High Definition 800 kHz ClearVü is ideal for 200' Max depth Scanning sonar

seo.ogDescription: The Garmin GT20-TM is a transducer that is ideal for shallow water fisherman looking for a trolling or transom mount transducer.
seo.title: Garmin GT20-TM | Transducer for Boat | GARMIN

010-01960-00.shippingDisclaimer: Ready to ship in 1–3 business days.

specs.Transducer frequency: Traditional 77/200; ClearVü CHIRP 455 kHz (435-475 kHz) & 800kHz (800-840 kHz)

overviewTab.content:
Perfect for the shallow water fisherman who want traditional and CHIRP ClearVü scanning sonar, this transom or trolling motor mounted transducer consistently displays fish arches as well as clear pictures of objects, structure and fish that pass below your boat.

The 20 ft transducer cable with built-in fast response temperature sensor has a power rating of 500 W; a depth of 1,900 ft (traditional) and 750 ft (ClearVü); an operating frequency of 77/200 kHz (traditional) and 455 kHz (ClearVü); and a 0 to 70 transom angle.

Transducer comes with transom and trolling motor mounts, and installation instructions. Follow the instructions carefully to avoid damaging your boat.

overviewTab.content:
GT22HW-TM transducer is perfect for freshwater fishermen who want CHIRP traditional sonar and CHIRP ClearVü scanning sonar. This transom or trolling motor mounted transducer consistently displays clear and crisp fish arches with superior target separation as well as clear definition of structure below the boat.

The 8-pin transducer features high wide band CHIRP traditional sonar (150-240 kHz) and has a power rating of 250 W. The CHIRP ClearVü (455/800 kHz) element has a power rating of 350 W.

GT22HW-TM is ideal for mounting to a trolling motor due to its compact size. For installation, follow the included instructions carefully to avoid damaging your boat.

seo.ogDescription: GT24UHD-TM is an all-in-one transducer that provides the highest resolution ClearVü scanning sonar images available as well as clear CHIRP traditional sonar.
seo.title: Garmin GT24UHD-TM | Ultra High-Definition Transducer

010-12908-00.shippingDisclaimer: Ready to ship in 1–3 business days.

specs.Transducer frequency: CHIRP High Wide (150-240 kHz); UHD ClearVü CHIRP 800 kHz (760-880 kHz)

overviewTab.content:
All-in-one Transducer

  • One transducer provides the highest resolution ClearVü scanning sonar images available and amazingly clear high wide CHIRP traditional sonar
  • High wide CHIRP traditional sonar provides remarkably clear target separation and definition
  • See incredibly detailed images of fish and structure up to 200’ below your boat with 800 kHz ClearVü sonar
  • Easy-to-install, compact, all-in-one design includes transom and trolling motor mounts

Ultra-clear View of What’s Below

The GT24 Ultra High-Definition all-in-one transducer provides image details so clear and precise, you can actually see fish hanging just off branches of submerged trees, brush and rocks. You can see the difference between bigger and smaller fish and even see individual fish swimming in bait balls. You get the highest resolution ClearVü scanning sonar images available plus amazingly clear high wide CHIRP traditional sonar1 — all in one transducer.

Ultra Performance

Ultra High-Definition scanning sonar shows you incredibly detailed images of fish and structure up to 200’ below your boat with 800 kHz ClearVü scanning sonar. It’s easy to install with included transom and trolling motor mounts so you can start fishing faster.

¹For use with GPSMAP® 8400xsv/8600xsv chartplotter/sonar combos
